<headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 23 at 2:21PM MDT  by NWS Billings</headline>
<description>...A cluster of thunderstorm will impact portions of extreme
southeastern Fallon and eastern Carter Counties through 245 PM MDT...
At 217 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of thunderstorms
10 miles west of West Short Pines, or 30 miles west of Buffalo,
moving east at 20 mph. Cool temperatures will allow small to medium
sized hail to develop.
HAZARD...Nickel size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.
Locations impacted include...
Alzada, Capitol, Albion and Mill Iron.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.88 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
